Responsibilities
· Analyzing the effectiveness and accuracy of data sources and data gathering techniques; Defining criteria for monitoring the integrity of data science models;
· Interacting with initiative leaders and pertinent teams to translate business needs into requirements for data, analytics, and data science solutions;
· Advancing data modeling and experimentation;
· Executing quality control procedures for analytical tools and techniques;
· Utilizing deep data science capabilities (such as machine learning and data mining) to create specialized and novel solutions;
· Creating the best practices in analytics, such as models, standards, and tools;
· Collaborating with pertinent functions to monitor how analytics are affecting business; and
· Providing technical direction on data architecture, data models, and data management while collaborating with the IT department and project managers.
Qualifications
Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience in quantative field (Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, etc.)
A suitable level of experience in a statistical and/or data science role;
Strong problem-solving skills with an emphasis on the development of data science products;
Experience using analytic tools and languages, such as Python, R, Matlab, PowerBI, Spotfire and SQL;
Eager to learn;
Experience working with large data sets and simulation/optimisation tools;
A good command of the English language;
Preferably experience and skills in project management; and
Preferably proficiency in one or more of the following data science areas: deep learning, reinforcement learning, machine learning, natural language processing, cloud computing and big data.

• Perform Flight Data Management (Standards Operating Procedure);
• Monitor Flight Occurrence Statistics and Trend report of turboprop Aircraft and report to coporate safety manager once a week;
• Collect and record flight occurrence data of turboprop Aircraft of every month, every 6 Month and every year.
• Analyse data and predict FDAP Trend;
• Verify and provide flight data record to pilots of a specific flight and FDAP Manager promptly;
• Present corrective action plan analysis result of FDAP data to FDAP Manager;
• Record and provide minute of FDAP (Flight Data Analysis Program) COMMITTEE Meeting;
• Assist FDAP Manager in representing safety systems and drivers the FDAP program forward;
• Perform other duties as required by superior.

Qualifications
• Bachelor’s degree in Aviation, engineering or related field
• More than 3 years operational knowledge and experience in the functions of an aviation organization
• Ability to write, speak, and read fluently in English and Thai
• Good analytical, presentation and management skills
• Good in Computer e.g. Microsoft Office
• Basic Knowledge of Airlines Safety
• Ability to read and understand flight data analysis program would be advantage
